# ARCHITECTURE CONTRACTS

## Layer responsibilities

### Voice server (port 8000)
- STT → intent classification → publish to jarvis.commands Redis stream
- Read from jarvis.updates Redis stream → TTS response
- NEVER owns mission truth. Stateless surface.

### Control plane (port 8001)
- FastAPI + SQLModel + PostgreSQL
- ONLY writer of mission state
- Reads jarvis.commands, routes to jarvis.execution, writes jarvis.receipts
- Manages approval queue, receipt store, SSE endpoint for UI

### Executor worker
- Reads jarvis.execution Redis stream
- Classifies intent with Ollama
- Takes action (webbrowser.open, etc.)
- Publishes result to jarvis.receipts
- NEVER writes to PostgreSQL directly — only through control plane API

### Command Center (port 5173)
- React/Vite frontend
- Reads from control plane REST + SSE
- Three-zone layout: left nav | center main | right sidebar
- Shows missions, approvals, receipts, logs, worker health

### Redis Streams (event bus)
- jarvis.commands — voice/UI → control plane
- jarvis.execution — control plane → executor
- jarvis.receipts — executor → control plane
- jarvis.updates — control plane → voice/UI

## Contracts
- State truth = PostgreSQL via control plane only
- Redis = fast cache + event bus only
- DashClaw = governance gate before risky actions
- No service talks to PostgreSQL except control plane